    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Emission of electromagnetic radiation, usually visible light, caused by excitation of atoms in a material, which then reemit almost immediately. The initial excitation is usually caused by absorption of energy from incident radiation or particles, such as X-rays or electrons.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
